          "body": "The entire chapter rests on one verse: *I have loved you with an everlasting love; therefore I have drawn you with lovingkindness*. The Hebrew is decisive — *ahavah olam* (love without temporal horizon) paired with *chesed* (covenant loyalty). The *therefore* matters: God's drawing of His people back from exile is not an emotional reaction to their improvement; it is the action of a love that *preceded* their unfaithfulness and outlasts it. Every promise in the chapter — gathering (31:8), rebuilding (31:4), new covenant (31:31), forgiveness (31:34) — is a derivative of 31:3. The chapter is asking the exile to read its own catastrophe through this prior love."
